						<summary>

						<p>Naṭarāja temple, west <hi rend="italic">gōpuram.</hi> right of entrance.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Sundara-pāṇḍya ••• ••••</hi></p>						

						<p>Three verses in praise of the king who was the lord of Madurai and an ardent Tamilaṉ. Refers to his victory over Vēṉāḍar, the northern kings and Koṅgar and to his killing Gaṇdagōpālaṇ, on whose death, his brothers heaped praise on him (Sundara-pāṇḍya).</p>						

